HEADWORD: Serration
<hw>Ser*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Condition of being serrate; formation in the shape of a
saw.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of the teeth in a serrate or serrulate
margin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Serratirostral</ent>⟦br⟧
